Been coming to this awesome Brooklyn eatery since it first opened. My husband and I were big fans of Mango Seed (same owners, few doors down) before ZuriLee opened its doors and were excited to try it out. Recently came here with a group of coworkers and am finally coming around to reviewing. Great space, amazing food (Oxtail Pizza is an absolute must), Drinks are delicious and their weekday Happy Hour goes until 9pm - I mean hello. 4/5 stars because the prices are a little steep for the size of the pizza. Oxtail Pizza is $26 I believe which I don't usually justify spending on a pizza. Overall, great place, right off the Q train, near the park and absolutely delicious.

The pizza here is unique with heavy Caribbean flavor influences. The Jerk Chicken and Oxtail pies are amazing. Great neighborhood spot for some non-traditional but delicious pizza.

What can I really say except that this restaurant is AWESOME. I have NEVER had pizza like this before. I grew up on big chain pizzas which is no comparison to ZuriLee pizza. My friends and I ordered the What the Pie, the Pinnacle and the Velvet. OMG to the 8th power. I am getting happy again just writing this. It can't be described in words, you just have to experience it for yourself. The decor and ambiance is very trendy and cool. I love the vibe. The staff is extremely friendly and attentive. This is definitely my new favorite restaurant. I can go here to hang with my girls, have a nice dinner with hubby or bring the kids for a treat. Highly recommended.

Restaurant in the heart of Flatbush. It's a Pizza Bar that has a great mix of what the neighborhood represents. I love that there is a mix of hipsters and long time residents. My pie had Lamb, mushrooms and pepperoni. It was delicious. Service was attentive and friendly. My only feedback is to make the pizza less soft and crisp it.

Have ordered delivery and eaten at restaurant.  Both were great.  The East Flatbush is a great pizza.  What I enjoy the most is the crust, it tastes incredible.  Plus they staff is friendly and they have a full cocktail menu with great beers on tap.  Will definitely be going back soon.

Zurilee is an awesome restaurant. Their great decor and atmosphere are exceeded by their quality staff, customer service and, most importantly, their food. It's been a neighborhood staple for me and my husband since it's opening - and now it's a spot we can also take our baby girl. Family friendly, date night appropriate, chilling with your crew, watch a game - whatever your occasion, Zurilee is the spot for you!

Me and my friend ate it all up; I kinda wish I ordered my own. Then we had the "What the pie" which has mushrooms, pepperoni, lamb, smoked mozzarella and Gouda. It's sooooooo goood!!
